@startuml concurrency-activity
title trade_baby_trade — Strategy Fan-out / Fan-in (scatter → reduce → join barrier)

skinparam conditionStyle inside

start
:IngestedDataset ready (read-only);
note right
  Shared across workers — fork / shared-memory,
  NOT re-serialized per task.
end note

:AnalysisEngine.executor.map(strategies, dataset);
note right: ProcessPoolExecutor (CPU-bound → bypass GIL)

fork
  partition "worker proc 1" {
    :Strategy A.evaluate(dataset);
    :emit signals_A;
  }
  :as_completed → selector.offer(signals_A);
fork again
  partition "worker proc 2" {
    :Strategy B.evaluate(dataset);
    :emit signals_B;
  }
  :as_completed → selector.offer(signals_B);
fork again
  partition "worker proc k" {
    :Strategy N.evaluate(dataset);
    :emit signals_N;
  }
  :as_completed → selector.offer(signals_N);
end fork

note right
  offer() runs as each future resolves —
  a streaming fold into a bounded heap that
  OVERLAPS the still-running strategies.
end note

:JOIN BARRIER — wait(ALL_COMPLETED, timeout);
if (any laggard past timeout?) then (yes)
  :cancel future + journal;
  :proceed in degraded mode;
else (no)
endif

:selector.finalize();
note right
  Barrier-time GLOBAL pass:
  DiversificationPolicy (max_per_instrument,
  max_gross_risk) needs ALL candidates →
  cannot pick TopN before the join.
end note
:deterministic sort (score, strategy_id);
note right: reproducible TopN despite\nnon-deterministic completion order
:ResultSet{ selected: TopN };
stop
@enduml
